{"word":"χιτωνίσκος","slug":"χιτωνίσκος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>χιτωνίσκος</b></el> <el>(χῐτωνίσκος, ὁ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:Diminutive'>Dim.</a> of <a href='S:χιτών'><el>χιτών</el></a>\n<p/><i>a short frock</i>, worn by men, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; of women, <i>a shift</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/>"}]}